2. IMPROVEMENTS MADE
---------------------
a) CHANGELOG.md — merge conflict artifact removed.
   A stray `=======` merge conflict separator was present between the v1.5.0
   and v1.4.0 entries, along with a duplicate introductory sentence. The
   conflicting lines were removed, restoring a clean, well-formed changelog.


3. RECOMMENDED IMPROVEMENTS (not implemented)
----------------------------------------------
a) .gitignore is Flutter-unaware.
   When the Flutter project is bootstrapped, the standard Flutter .gitignore
   entries should be added (e.g. .dart_tool/, build/, *.g.dart, pubspec.lock
   for apps, .flutter-plugins, .flutter-plugins-dependencies, etc.).
   Recommendation: expand .gitignore at Flutter project bootstrap time.

b) ai submodule uses an SSH remote URL (git@github.com:egohygiene/ai.git).
   SSH URLs require an SSH key to be available in CI. If the GitHub Actions
   runners do not have the deploy key configured, `git submodule update --init`
   will fail. Consider switching to the HTTPS URL
   (https://github.com/egohygiene/ai.git) for CI compatibility, or ensure
   the appropriate deploy key / PAT is provisioned as a repository secret.

c) ai submodule is not initialised.
   The ai/ directory is empty. Any workflow rules referenced from
   ai/factory/workflow/ are not currently accessible. Initialise the
   submodule (`git submodule update --init`) to make those rules available.

d) CHANGELOG.md missing blank line before v1.3.0 entry.
   The separator blank line between the v1.4.0 and v1.3.0 sections is absent.
   This is cosmetic and does not affect functionality; semantic-release will
   regenerate the file on the next release.

e) package.json version field is 0.0.0.
   This is intentional for semantic-release-managed repositories (the field
   is not used for versioning), but it can cause confusion. A comment or note
   in CONTRIBUTING.md clarifying this may help new contributors.

f) release.yml lacks an explicit id-token or attestation step.
   For supply-chain integrity, consider adding OIDC-based attestation or
   Sigstore signing of release artifacts in a future iteration.

g) No branch protection or CODEOWNERS configuration detected.
   Adding branch protection rules on main (require PR review, require status
   checks) and a CODEOWNERS file would improve governance before the Flutter
   project grows in team size.


4. NOTES AFFECTING UPCOMING FLUTTER SETUP
------------------------------------------
- Flutter SDK is not yet installed or pinned. Decide on a version pinning
  strategy (fvm, asdf, or a hardcoded version in pubspec.yaml) before
  bootstrapping the project.
- The current semantic-release configuration releases only from `main`. If a
  Flutter project adopts a more branchy workflow (e.g. release/* branches),
  the branches array in .releaserc.json will need updating.
- The commitlint type-enum does not include `flutter`-specific scopes; scopes
  are optional and free-form so no change is required, but team conventions
  around scope naming (e.g. `ui`, `data`, `core`) should be agreed early.
- The ai/ submodule must be initialised before any AI factory workflow rules
  can be read or enforced.


5. CONCLUSION
-------------
The repository is clean and structurally sound for a pre-Flutter state.
The only active defect found was the merge conflict artifact in CHANGELOG.md,
which has been resolved. All remaining items are recommendations for the
Flutter bootstrap or subsequent iterations. No CI or release workflows were
broken by this audit.
